---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const REPO_URL = "https://github.com/kevinhegg/tweetsie-app"; // TODO: replace with your repo
const SITE_URL = "https://tweetsie.app"; // or tweetsy.app if that’s the one
---
<BaseLayout title="[Collections as Data] for Apps" desc="Staging">
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Collections as Data for Apps</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 mb-6">
    One-hour collaborative, prompt-driven build in Cursor. We start from a Hello World page and
    have <code>/data</code> + <code>/public/images</code> pre-staged for speed.
  </p>

  <div class="grid gap-4">
    <section class="bg-white border rounded-xl p-4">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">Plan (approx.)</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal ml-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
        <li>Warm-up: “Snake eats HELLO WORLD” on the homepage.</li>
        <li>Wire <code>items.json</code> (client-side fetch) and render a minimal list.</li>
        <li>Audience-driven: filters (subjects, years), details page, CSV export, etc.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-white border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">Starting point</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
        <li>Repo: <a class="underline" href={REPO_URL}>{REPO_URL}</a></li>
        <li>Site: <a class="underline" href={SITE_URL}>{SITE_URL}</a></li>
        <li>Data staged in <code>/data</code> (and can copy to <code>/public/data/items.json</code> on build).</li>
        <li>Images staged in <code>/public/images/</code>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-white border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">Notes</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
        <li>No server required; pure client-side Astro + Tailwind.</li>
        <li>We’ll write prompts together and let Cursor implement.</li>
        <li>Scope: prototype only; can refine after the session.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
